<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<ScrollView xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    xmlns:app="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res-auto"
    xmlns:tools="http://schemas.android.com/tools"
    android:layout_width="match_parent"
    android:layout_height="match_parent"
    tools:context=".topic17"
    android:background="@color/silver">

    <RelativeLayout
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content">

        <ImageView
            android:id="@+id/img"
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:src="@drawable/fr"
            android:adjustViewBounds="true"/>

        <TextView
            android:id="@+id/title"
            android:layout_below="@+id/img"
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:text="FRONTEND AND BACKEND SERVICES"
            android:textSize="20dp"
            android:layout_marginTop="10dp"
            android:layout_marginBottom="10dp"
            android:textStyle="bold"
            android:textAlignment="center"
            android:textColor="#000000"/>

        <android.support.v7.widget.CardView
            android:layout_below="@id/title"
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:layout_margin="20dp"
            app:cardCornerRadius="8dp"
            app:cardElevation="10dp">

            <LinearLayout
                android:layout_below="@+id/title"
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:orientation="vertical">


                <TextView
                    android:padding="10dp"
                    android:lineSpacingExtra="3dp"
                    android:textSize="16dp"
                    android:layout_width="match_parent"
                    android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                    android:text="
Web development governs all the code that makes a website tick. It can be split into two
categories-"
                    android:textColor="@color/black"
                    android:textAlignment="center"/>

                <TextView
                    android:padding="10dp"
                    android:lineSpacingExtra="3dp"
                    android:textSize="16dp"
                    android:layout_width="match_parent"
                    android:textStyle="bold"
                    android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                    android:text="
1. Front-End development which is client side devlopment"
                    android:textColor="@color/black"
                    android:layout_marginTop="15dp"
                    android:textAlignment="center"/>

                <TextView
                    android:padding="10dp"
                    android:lineSpacingExtra="3dp"
                    android:textStyle="bold"
                    android:textSize="16dp"
                    android:layout_width="match_parent"
                    android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                    android:text="
2. Back-End development which is server side development"
                    android:layout_marginTop="15dp"
                    android:textColor="@color/black"
                    android:textAlignment="center"/>

                <TextView
                    android:padding="10dp"
                    android:lineSpacingExtra="3dp"
                    android:layout_marginTop="15dp"
                    android:textSize="16dp"
                    android:layout_width="match_parent"
                    android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                    android:text="
'Front-End' or client side of an application is the code responsible for determining how the
website will actually display, designs mocked up by a designer. Front-End of a website is the
part that interact with users."
                    android:textColor="@color/black"
                    android:textAlignment="center"/>

                <TextView
                    android:padding="10dp"
                    android:lineSpacingExtra="3dp"
                    android:textSize="16dp"
                    android:layout_marginTop="15dp"
                    android:layout_width="match_parent"
                    android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                    android:text="
Front-End devs must be adept at three main languages : HTML, CSS and Javascript programming.
In addition to fluency in these languages, front-end devs needs to be familiar with frameworks
like Bootstrap, Foundation, backbone, Angular Js and Ember Js."
                    android:textColor="@color/black"
                    android:textAlignment="center"/>

                <TextView
                    android:padding="10dp"
                    android:lineSpacingExtra="3dp"
                    android:textSize="16dp"
                    android:layout_width="match_parent"
                    android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                    android:layout_marginTop="15dp"
                    android:text="
'Back-End' or server side development controls what goes behind the scenes of a web application.
A back-end often uses a database to generate the front-end."
                    android:textColor="@color/black"
                    android:textAlignment="center"/>

                <TextView
                    android:padding="10dp"
                    android:lineSpacingExtra="3dp"
                    android:textSize="16dp"
                    android:layout_width="match_parent"
                    android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                    android:layout_marginTop="15dp"
                    android:text="
In order to make server, application and database communicate with each other, Back-End
developers use server scripting languages like PHP, Ruby, PERL, JAVA, Node.Js, and Python to
build an application."
                    android:textColor="@color/black"
                    android:textAlignment="center"/>

                <ImageView
                    android:layout_marginTop="10dp"
                    android:layout_marginBottom="10dp"
                    android:padding="25dp"
                    android:layout_gravity="center"
                    android:adjustViewBounds="true"
                    android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                    android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                    android:src="@drawable/fr2"/>

            </LinearLayout>

        </android.support.v7.widget.CardView>

    </RelativeLayout>

</ScrollView>